      <abstract displayLabel="Abstract">This guide was assembled to aid change agents, such as research and
                trade organizations, in evaluating potential research and development investments in
                the manufacturing industry. It includes an overview of the primary methods used for
                evaluating investments in manufacturing technologies along with tailoring methods
                for change agent investments. The process presented in this guide has 5 steps with
                each step having a section of the guide dedicated to it.</abstract>
